HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 325
BY REPRESENTATIVE BAYHAM
A RESOLUTION
To commemorate Sail 250 New Orleans and the arrival of the tall ships of the world in New
Orleans from May 28 through June 1, 2026, in honor of the two hundred fiftieth
anniversary of the United States of America.
WHEREAS, New Orleans will be the first stop as America welcomes the tall ships
of the world to the Port of New Orleans for a nationwide celebration of the two hundred
fiftieth anniversary of the United States of America; and
WHEREAS, from May 28 through June 1, 2026, the city will celebrate the
Sestercentennial of America with the largest-ever flotilla of tall ships from around the world;
and
WHEREAS, Sail 250 New Orleans will bring a majestic nautical spectacle to the
historic Mississippi River and host a diverse array of events, festivities, and celebrations
across the region to educate, entertain, and engage audiences from communities across the
country; and
WHEREAS, the Port of New Orleans will welcome twelve tall ships and naval
vessels from Argentina, Chile, Colombia, the Netherlands, Peru, Sweden, the United
Kingdom, the United States, and Uruguay; and
WHEREAS, the U.S. Coast Guard Cutter Eagle is regarded as "America's Tall Ship"
and is homeported in New London, Connecticut; it is a two hundred ninety-five-foot, three-
masted barque that carries twenty-two thousand square feet of sail and has a core crew of
eight officers and fifty enlisted members; it remains the only active square-rigger in U.S.
government service and always leads the Parade of Sail in U.S. port visits; and
