WHEREAS, USS Kearsage is a versatile amphibious assault ship designed to project
power from sea to shore and carries Marines, aircraft, and landing craft in a single integrated
platform; the ship has a flight deck that resembles a small aircraft carrier and a floodable
well deck for amphibious operations, and it serves as a floating hub for rapid-response
military and humanitarian missions worldwide; and
WHEREAS, USS Farragut is a multi-mission guided missile destroyer built to defend
against air, surface, and subsurface threats while operating independently or as a part of a
carrier strike group; the ship is equipped with the Aegis Combat System and a versatile array
of missiles and sensors, and it delivers precision, speed, and adaptability across modern
naval operations; and
WHEREAS, USCGC Mohawk is a medium endurance cutter built for long-range
patrols, specialization in law enforcement, search and rescue, and maritime security
missions; the ship features a balanced mix of endurance, speed, and seakeeping and serves
as a reliable workhorse on extended operations across coastal and international waters; and
WHEREAS, HMS Trent is a modern offshore patrol vessel built for persistent global
presence, conducting maritime security, counter-smuggling, and patrol missions far from
home waters; the ship is designed for efficiency and endurance and combines a relatively
small crew with advanced sensors and a flexible mission deck to operate independently for
extended deployments; and
WHEREAS, it is with great pride that the state of Louisiana recognizes the tall ships
and naval vessels of the world during the landmark celebration of the two hundred fiftieth
anniversary of the nation.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commemorate Sail 250 New Orleans and the arrival
of the tall ships of the world in New Orleans from May 28 through June 1, 2026, in honor
of the two hundred fiftieth anniversary of the United States of America and does hereby
encourage citizens to join in the celebration of the storied maritime history of the nation.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
